9
Key Responsibilities

 Strategic Leadership
 Define and execute operations strategy aligned with business growth goals.
 Partner with the CSCO to shape long-term planning for Inventory, logistics, supply chain, and fulfillment.
 Drive innovation in operational models, leveraging technology, automation, and data-led decision-making.

Key KPIs

 Business outcome of P&L: Top line delivery for each channel: Purplle.com and Purplle stores
 Availability of Inventory at Stores/ Dark Stores/ FC level as per consumer demand
 Consumer Delivery: Speed (Order to Deliver), ON Time performance against promise (At WH & Logistics level)
 Cost of operations : Cost per order for B2C, Movement cost per unit for B2B Demand & Supply Planning
 Leading a team of Demand & Supply Planning to ensure we are able to forecast Demand in all service nodes of Retail stores, Dark Stores, Fulfillment center and able to maintain good on-shelf availability of products across TP (Third Party Brands) and Private Brands
 Manage sourcing & distribution of TP brand products from Brand House
 Manage distribution of Private Brands

Logistics Management

 Oversee end-to-end Logistics for B2B (Sourcing, Inter-warehouse movement, movement to retail stores/ dark stores) and B2C (Consumer Delivery of orders)
 Build and optimize a scalable distribution network for urban and non-urban market.
 Partner with 3PLs, transporters, and warehouse service providers to deliver service reliability and cost efficiency.

Warehouse & Fulfillment Operations

 Lead warehouse strategy, design, and execution across multiple locations including DC/FC/ Dark Stores & Retail stores.
 Drive inventory accuracy, throughput optimization, and SLA adherence.
 Champion automation, layout optimization, safety, compliance, and sustainability standards.

Team & Stakeholder Management

 Build, mentor, and lead large cross-functional operations teams across geographies.
 Partner with CXOs, category, finance, and technology teams to deliver customer-first operations.
 Establish clear KPIs, monitor performance, and drive accountability across the operations function.
 Process Excellence & Risk Management
 Champion continuous improvement using Lean, Six Sigma, and other operational excellence frameworks.
 Build and implement robust risk management and business continuity frameworks.
 Set up governance, SOPs, and strong internal controls for scalable and compliant operations.

Customer-Centric Execution

 Ensure the customer promise is consistently met through best-in-class fulfillment and delivery.
 Drive core metrics such as On-Time Delivery, OTIF (On Time In Full), and Customer Satisfaction.

Qualifications & Experience

 15+ years of progressive leadership in operations, supply chain, logistics, and warehouse management.
 Strong exposure to both e-commerce/ Quick Commerce and Retail ecosystems

(preferred: dual experience).

 Proven success in managing large-scale, multi-location operations in dynamic environments.
 Hands-on people leadership experience, with ability to inspire large, diverse teams.
 Strong analytical mindset with demonstrated expertise in automation, process optimization, and cost transformation.
 MBA/PGDM in Operations, Supply Chain, or equivalent preferred.

Key Competencies

 Strategic yet execution-focused leadership.
 High adaptability and ability to thrive in ambiguous, high-growth environments.
 Strong stakeholder management and communication skills.
 Results-oriented with a sharp focus on efficiency, cost, and customer experience.
